Fantasy Football Scoring

How scoring systems and roster settings affect positional value
PPR Points Per Reception: STD (0), HPPR (0.5), PPR (1.0). Shown as columns in the grid
PFD Poins Per First Down: STD (0), HPFD (0.5), PFD (1.0). Shown as rows in the grid
Rank Nth best player by position.
Raw Points Total fantasy points scored during season. In all plots, the solid line is the average across all years selected, while the bands indicate the range of values observed.
Relative Value Points are converted to points-over-replacement, depending on the roster rules selected. Total value is calculated by summing all positive points-over-replacement across all positions. Relative value is calculated by using this total to normalize the points over replacement
RB Baseline For each position, the ratio of the relative value to the relative value of running backs is calculated. In these plots, the average relative value of RBs is always equal to 1.
Roster Settings Change roster settings to update the relative value plots (nQB=[1,2], nRB=[1,2,3,4], nWR=[1,2,3,4], nTE=[1,2], nFlex=[1,2,3,4], nTeams=[8,10,12,14]). Flex positions can be any of RB/WR/TE.

Raw data was collected from ESPN (Passing, Rushing, Receiving, Scoring).

Interactive plots were created using Bokeh. Code is available on GitHub.
